Sterna without modifications, broad, flat, poorly setose (Fig. 1
H-J
). Stigma openings flat, beset with dense and long filaments (Fig. 1N). Legs in ♀ and juveniles clearly shorter and slenderer, ca 1.0-1.1 times as long as body height, in ♂ somewhat incrassate and ca 1.3-1.4 times as long as body height (Figs 1B, 2A); tarsi longest; sphaerotrichomes missing (Fig. 2A). Each ♂ coxa 2 with a short, cylindrical, distoventral gonapophysis.
